{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idf3dbdd40-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc","identifier":"/us/usc/t35/s304"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"304"},"text":"§ 304.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Reexamination order by Director","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"If, in a determination made under the provisions of subsection 303(a), the Director finds that a substantial new question of patentability affecting any claim of a patent is raised, the determination will include an order for reexamination of the patent for resolution of the question. The patent owner will be given a reasonable period, not less than two months from the date a copy of the determination is given or mailed to him, within which he may file a statement on such question, including any amendment to his patent and new claim or claims he may wish to propose, for consideration in the reexamination. If the patent owner files such a statement, he promptly will serve a copy of it on the person who has requested reexamination under the provisions of section 302. Within a period of two months from the date of service, that person may file and have considered in the reexamination a reply to any statement filed by the patent owner. That person promptly will serve on the patent owner a copy of any reply filed.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idf3dbdd41-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/517/s1"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–517, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-12-12"},"text":"Dec. 12, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/3016"},"text":"94 Stat. 3016","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/113/dB/s1000/a/9/tIV/s4732/a/10/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–113, div. B, § 1000(a)(9) [title IV, § 4732(a)(10)(A)]","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1999-11-29"},"text":"Nov. 29, 1999","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/113/1536"},"text":"113 Stat. 1536","children":[],"tail":", 1501A–582; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/273/dC/tIII/s13206/b/1/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–273, div. C, title III, § 13206(b)(1)(B)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-11-02"},"text":"Nov. 2, 2002","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/116/1906"},"text":"116 Stat. 1906","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/29/s20/j"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–29, § 20(j)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-09-16"},"text":"Sept. 16, 2011","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/125/335"},"text":"125 Stat. 335","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idf3dbdd42-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idf3dbdd43-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idf3dbdd44-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2011—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/29"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–29","children":[],"tail":" struck out “of this title” after “303(a)” and after “302”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2002—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/273"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–273","children":[],"tail":" made technical correction to directory language of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/